cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on improving the performance of online grasp planning algorithms for robotic systems by incorporating reachability into the planning process. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper may involve computer vision techniques for analyzing the planning scene and identifying reachable regions. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper may involve AI techniques for optimizing the grasp planning process and selecting the most appropriate grasps for a given situation. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper may involve machine learning techniques for training the grasp planner and/or for analyzing the feasibility of end-effector poses. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper may involve control theory techniques for ensuring that the resulting grasps are stable and can be executed successfully.
